title: Irish-Israeli woman who went missing after Hamas attack confirmed dead
description: An Irish-Israeli woman who went missing after Hamas attacked a music festival at the weekend has been confirmed dead.

title: 'We brought the tank, we launched a missile': Border guard volunteers led initial fight against Hamas - who could still be hiding in Israel | Stuart Ramsay
description: Shortly before 9pm on Tuesday evening, a Hamas fighter attempted to kill an Israeli soldier with a knife.

title: King expresses 'deep shock' in call with Israel's president  - as Prince William says he is 'profoundly distressed'
description: The King has expressed his condolences and "deep shock" at the "barbaric" actions by Hamas in a call with Israel's president - as Prince William said he was "profoundly distressed" by the "horrors" inflicted.

title: NASA reveals 'incredible' findings from asteroid that could explain origins of life on Earth
description: NASA has revealed its "incredible" findings from a sample that was scooped up from the surface of an asteroid and delivered to Earth by spacecraft.

title: How Hamas militants prepared for brutal ground assault on Israel-Gaza border
description: Hamas has released a video showing how it trained to destroy barriers on the Israel-Gaza border, allowing it to begin its mass slaughter of civilians.

title: What an Israeli ground offensive against Hamas would look like
description: Israel could be just "hours or days" from launching a ground offensive against Hamas in Gaza, according to Sky's security and defence analyst Michael Clarke.

title: BA suspends Tel Aviv flights after Hamas says it attacked airport
description: British Airways (BA) has suspended flights to Tel Aviv - after Hamas said it had attacked the Israeli airport.

title: Huge planetary collision discovered after 'unusual event' spotted by amateur astronomer
description: An explosive collision between two icy giant planets has been discovered, after being spotted on a social media post by an amateur astronomer.

title: UK's foreign secretary runs for cover in Israel after siren warning of rocket attack goes off
description: Foreign Secretary James Cleverly had to run for cover in Israel, with air raid sirens heard ringing out in the background warning of an incoming rocket attack.

title: 'Extraordinary' step as monkey with pig's kidney lives for two years
description: A monkey has survived more than two years with a pig's kidney - with experts saying the "extraordinary" result gives hope for their use in humans.

title: From the sky and on the ground: Gaza destruction revealed after Israeli strikes
description: As Israel continues to pound the Gaza Strip with missile strikes, satellite imagery has revealed the extent of damage.

title: Gaza runs out of electricity as 'major strikes' launched against Israeli city
description: Besieged Gaza has run out of electricity as Israel continues its bombardment in response to a brutal Hamas attack over the weekend.

title: Royal state visit to Kenya will acknowledge 'painful aspects' of shared history
description: The King and Queen will make a state visit to Kenya at the end of October to help shore up relations with the Commonwealth.

title: 'It's important to separate the facts from speculation': What we actually know about the viral report of beheaded babies in Israel
description: Reports that Israeli soldiers discovered babies that had been beheaded in the Kfar Aza kibbutz are circulating on social and traditional media outlets around the world.

title: Climate crisis will change taste of beer and make it more expensive, say scientists
description: Beer quality is on a steady decline and is likely to cost more at the bar because of climate change, a new study has found.

title: Apple issues iPhone 12 software update in France over radiation concerns
description: Apple has said it plans to update the iPhone 12's software after France halted sales of the model over fears about excessive radiation levels.

title: Children among 17 British nationals feared dead or missing in Israel
description: Seventeen British nationals, including children, are feared dead or missing in Israel after an attack by Hamas, Sky News understands.

title: Man arrested over wildfires engulfing central Argentina as dozens evacuated
description: A 27-year-old man has been detained in Argentina, after wildfires engulfed the country's Cordoba province amid an intense heat wave.

title: Daredevil, 104, dies one week after becoming 'world's oldest skydiver'
description: A 104-year-old skydiver - who could be certified as the oldest person to ever jump out of a plane - has died just a week after a daredevil stunt.

title: Homes destroyed after another earthquake hits Afghanistan
description: Hundreds of homes have been flattened as another earthquake shook a part of western Afghanistan on Wednesday morning - just days after more than 2,445 died in an earlier quake.

title: US sends hostage experts to help Israel get its people back from Gaza
description: The US has sent a team of technical experts to Israel to assist in hostage recovery , according to official sources.
